What about the case when we are doing a host build? Then neither is defined and we'll hit the #error. 
To also address the response to the next comment, I think we can have the following set of cases (of defined variables):
1) ART_TARGET and ART_TARGET_LINUX -> (kIsTargetLinux) = true
2) ART_TARGET and ART_TARGET_ANDROID -> false
3) ART_TARGET and !ART_TARGET_LINUX and !ART_TARGET_ANDROID-> error
5) !ART_TARGET and ART_TARGET_LINUX -> error
6) !ART_TARGET and ART_TARGET_ANDROID -> error
7) !ART_TARGET and !ART_TARGET_LINUX and !ART_TARGET_ANDROID -> false (host case, no error)
5 and 6 can be conflated (with an or) to simplify things.

